ents and can overall make seeking medical care a much more daunting task. This in turn can again make people that use ASL less likely to receive appropriate levels of medical care.%0a%3c  %0a%3c The article from the American Psychological Association includes that varying degrees of hearing loss are becoming more prevalent, so the issues present for those hard of hearing may become critical for a larger share of the population if the use of ASL rises. %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
